Product Manager - Macquarie Investment Management (Global Listed Infrastructure) - New York at Macquarie • JOFDAV
























This job listing has expired and the position may no longer be open for hire.






    Product Manager - Macquarie Investment Management (Global Listed Infrastructure) - New York
      at Macquarie
  

    Posted in Other over 1 year ago.
  

      This job brought to you by America's Job Exchange


Type: Full Time
Location: New York, New York
  
Job Description:
RECRUITER: Tammy Lee
	Macquarie Asset Management (MAM; formerly known as Macquarie Funds Group) is a full-service asset manager, offering a diverse range of products including securities investment management, infrastructure and real asset management, and fund and equity-based structured products.
	MAM comprises the following three divisions:
      Macquarie Infrastructure and Real Assets
      Macquarie Investment Management
      Macquarie Specialised Investment Solutions.
	The Global Listed Infrastructure team of Macquarie Asset Management has developed a reputation as a leader in providing Global Listed Infrastructure solutions to clients.  The team manages over $2bln via mutual funds, sub-advisory relationships and institutional separate accounts. The team consists of 19 professionals located in New York and Sydney. As the team continues to grow its US client base, we are seeking a Jr. Product Manager to support our increased marketing and client service activities.
	You will have a minimum of two years experience in an investment firm, mutual fund or hedge fund, in a client service, marketing support or product management role. Your primary focus will be supporting the team through client reporting, quantitative analysis, investment commentary.
	 In this dynamic and multi-faceted role, you will be responsible for:
	* Working directly with the investment team on a variety of marketing and client related tasks and have specific responsibilities ensuring that all client reports are produced and delivered to clients accurately and in line with deadlines
	* Undertaking quantitative tasks, such as calculation of portfolio performance characteristics; analysis of index performance 
 	* Assisting in the development of marketing materials and presentations to support existing clients and help generate new business opportunities
 	* Working with Macquarie Investment Management global distribution teams to provide investment information as needed
 	* Writing investment commentary reports for our investment strategies
 	* Handling Public Relations requests in relation to our NYSE listed funds
	To succeed in this role you will:
	* Be a team player, willing and eager to communicate with our teammates in both New York and Sydney
 	* Understand the key quantitative concepts of portfolio management
 	* Possess strong spreadsheet and quantitative skills; experience with FactSet or Bloomberg is an advantage, but not essential (as training will be provided)
 	* Possess strong writing skills and an ability to communicate complex ideas in understandable language
 	* Ability to maintain strong attention to detail coupled with a sense of urgency
 	* Be able to work with limited supervision on multiple tasks
 	* Progress towards the CFA or CAIA designations is a plus
	This role represents an opportunity to be part of a high calibre team, with the potential for meaningful growth in the future.  We invite applications from candidates wanting to help us drive our success.
	All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment and will not be discriminated against on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, protected veteran status, genetic information, marital status, gender identity or any other impermissible criterion or circumstance. Macquarie also takes affirmative action in support of its policy to hire and advance in employment individuals who are minorities, women, protected veterans, and individuals with disabilities.  
	 ADVERTISED: 18 Mar 2016  Eastern Standard Time
APPLICATIONS CLOSE:
